n have the awards to prove it. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Dev Experience<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>The bulk of my development experience is with PHP-based content management systems (<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/wordpress.org\\\">WordPress<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/expressionengine.com\\\">ExpressionEngine<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/craftcms.com\\\">Craft<\\/a>) and workflow apps built in Java, Python and Rails.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>While not the sexiest of platforms from a technical perspective, WordPress has been a strong focus for the past few years given it\'s 25% market share of the the internet. It was a practical choice and despite its reputation for spaghetti code under-the-hood, my team and I have found ways to bend and shape it to our needs while applying some architectural best-practices from our favorite frameworks.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This site was built in Craft CMS which I quickly grew to love, and I\'ll recommend to anyone willing to deviate from the (relative) comfort of WordPress.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>As of 2016, I am building my first app in <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/laravel.com\\\">Laravel<\\/a> and enjoying almost every aspect of it. Despite having written it since the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Dynamic_HTML\\\">DHTML<\\/a> days, I maintain a love\\/hate relationship with JavaScript and struggle to find motivation to keep up with what seems like a framework&nbsp;fashion show.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Looking Ahead<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>CRUD apps and CMS platforms are becoming commoditized, so I find myself motivated, by curiosity and pragmatism, to continue to branch out. Areas of interest are machine learning and functional programming. For the first part of 2017 I\'ll be focusing on Erlang, subsequently Elixir, and hopefully building my first app in Phoenix. There are Clojure and Haskell books stacking up on my desk once that\'s done.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Evenings & Weekends<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\\"dropcap\\\">O<\\/span>utside of work, I spend as much time as possible outdoors. This usually ends up as some combination of hiking, climbing, blazing trails, backpacking or camping and usually with some combination of my wife and dog.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I have been a hobby photographer since 2007 and as of 2016 I have sold all my digital gear to start shooting film. Check out some of my work if you\'re interested.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Time and finances permitting, I travel as much as I can. I\'ve been to places as far flung as Iceland, New Zealand, Tibet and New Jersey. On the shortlist are Kilimanjaro and Patagonia, which should round out all continents, Antarctica notwithstanding.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Alright, that\'s all I\'ve got for now. If you want to find out more you can follow me using one of the links in the footer or send me an <a href=\\\"mailto:nate.luzod@gmail.com\\\">old fashioned email<\\/a>.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2017-02-26 20:19:53', '2017-02-26 20:19:53', 'ff239966-61c3-45d4-80b4-62e82be59068'),
