ccording to the perfect fourth <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.modularscale.com\\/\\\">modular scale<\\/a> with a maximum column width of 580px for optimal legibility. Color palette (and likely more) is inspired by <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/edwardtufte.github.io\\/tufte-css\\/\\\">Tufte CSS<\\/a>. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>JavaScript is primarily vanilla but a few NPM&nbsp;modules have been <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.npmjs.com\\/package\\/prismjs\\\">thrown<\\/a> in and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/browserify.org\\/\\\">Browserified<\\/a> for assistance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bourbon.io\\/\\\">Bourbon<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/neat.bourbon.io\\/\\\">Neat<\\/a> were used to write styles which were compiled with <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/gulpjs.com\\/\\\">Gulp<\\/a> and and served from Amazon S3. Code is served from my platform of choice, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/heroku.com\\\">Heroku<\\/a>. &nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2017-02-27 03:31:28', '2017-02-27 03:31:28', 'c403bbf1-646f-4a9c-b682-a00c4c0292fc'),
